President Muhammadu Buhari has met with leaders of the All Progressives Congress (APC) from the Southwest, led by Chief Bisi Akande. Presidency sources informed that the meeting was private but was ostensibly on matters concerning the ruling party. It took place at the president’s office in the presidential villa, Abuja with no media coverage allowed. Apart from Chief Akande, others who attended the meeting are the Chief of Staff to the President, Prof. Ibrahim Gambari, Chief Segun Osoba, Prince Tajudeen Olusi and Dr Abayomi Finnih. Chief Akande and Chief Osoba declined to speak on the meeting when approached by State House reporters as they emerged from the president’s office. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE Fayose congratulates Obaseki, warns him against returning to APC(Opens in a new browser tab) Obaseki who joined the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in June after he was disqualified by the APC, defeated Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu of the APC in the election results announced by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) on Sunday.private meeting Post COVID-19: Kano based industrialist tasks FG on economy A Kano based industrialist, Chief Kalu Ogbonnaya, has advised the Federal Government to take necessary steps to stimulate the nation’s economy to prevent a recession post COVID-19.private meeting Ogbonnaya who spoke in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Thursday in Kano, said as a result of the coronavirus raving the world, no business has been moving.private meeting  private meeting NIGERIAN TRIBUNE  SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that
